This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with improving the performance of a sequence-to-sequence model for Voice Search. It may also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with speech recognition. Additionally, it involves exploring language models and attention mechanisms, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, since the paper deals with a streaming model, it may also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
